    -- The number of possible squares between 2n and 4n is at most 2*sqrt(4n) - 2*sqrt(2n) + 1 < 51 for n >= 100
    -- But we can use known result: in any subset of [n,2n] of size >= 51, there are two distinct elements summing to a square
